ZH: 阎王是中国传统信仰中的地狱之王。
EN: Yan Wang is the king of hell in traditional Chinese beliefs.

ZH: 传说阎王每天都要审判来世的鬼魂。
EN: Legend has it that Yan Wang judges the souls of the deceased every day.

ZH: 阎王殿是奈何桥的另一边。
EN: The Palace of Yan Wang is on the other side of the Naihe Bridge.

ZH: 人们相信，死后会去见阎王。
EN: People believe that they will meet Yan Wang after death.

ZH: 在中国民间故事中，阎王经常出现在夜晚。
EN: In Chinese folk tales, Yan Wang often appears during the night.

ZH: 阎王的面孔被形容得非常丑陋可怖。
EN: The face of Yan Wang is described as extremely hideous and terrifying.

ZH: 有人说，阎王的手掌是烧红的。
EN: Some say that the palms of Yan Wang are burning red.

ZH: 阎王会根据人们的善恶判决他们的来世。
EN: Yan Wang judges people's afterlives based on their good and evil deeds.

ZH: 其他神明也必须服从阎王的命令。
EN: Other deities must obey the orders of Yan Wang as well.

ZH: 传说中，只有孟婆汤才能让鬼魂忘记前世，才不会惹恼阎王。
EN: According to legend, only the soup from Meng Po can make the souls forget their past lives and not provoke Yan Wang.

ZH: 阎王的咒语被认为有着无比的力量。
EN: The spells of Yan Wang are believed to possess immense power.

ZH: 惊吓别人是会惹怒阎王的。
EN: Scaring others would anger Yan Wang.

ZH: 他们认为阎王能够惩罚恶人，保护善良的人。
EN: They believe that Yan Wang can punish the wicked and protect the good-hearted.

ZH: 一直到见到阎王，才能知道自己下辈子的去向。
EN: One will not know one's destination in the next life until meeting Yan Wang.

ZH: 在中国文化中，人们对阎王有着敬畏之情。
EN: In Chinese culture, people have a sense of awe towards Yan Wang.

ZH: 有人说，一旦你见到阎王，你就无法再回到人间。
EN: Some say that once you meet Yan Wang, you can never return to the human world.

ZH: 逃避阎王的审判是不可能的。
EN: It is impossible to escape the judgment of Yan Wang.

ZH: 阎王有时会派遣地府的鬼卒抓捕罪人。
EN: Yan Wang sometimes sends underworld guards to capture criminals.

ZH: 阎王的话语具有绝对的权威。
EN: The words of Yan Wang carry absolute authority.

ZH: 传说阎王有一张无底洞一样的嘴巴。
EN: Legend has it that Yan Wang has a mouth like a bottomless pit.
